                            <comment id="16331889" author="jensg" created="Fri, 19 Jan 2018 08:19:52 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And access for unit&#160;Character may be&#160;determined through defiine symbol&#160;OLD_UNIT_NAMES&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Why?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16332593" author="antontramp" created="Fri, 19 Jan 2018 17:37:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Full unit name System.Character. This unit added&#160;in Thrift.Utils by scheme&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;uses&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160; {$IFDEF OLD_UNIT_NAMES}&lt;br/&gt;
&#160; Classes, Windows, SysUtils, &lt;b&gt;Character&lt;/b&gt;, SyncObjs;&lt;br/&gt;
&#160; {$ELSE}&lt;br/&gt;
&#160; System.Classes, Winapi.Windows, System.SysUtils, &lt;b&gt;System.Character&lt;/b&gt;, System.SyncObjs;&lt;br/&gt;
&#160; {$ENDIF}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If condition&#160;OLD_UNIT_NAMES is not defined then compiler will require fully unit name. And&#160;identifier Character.IsLowSurrogate&#160;will not be defined unlike&#160;identifier System.Character.IsLowSurrogate&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16332691" author="jensg" created="Fri, 19 Jan 2018 18:26:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed, thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
